A N A C T
RELATING TO HEALTH AND SAFETY -- LICENSING OF HEALTHCARE FACILITIES
Introduced By: Senators Kallman, Gu, DiMario, Ciccone, Vargas, and Lauria
Date Introduced: February 13, 2025
Referred To: Senate Finance
It is enacted by the General Assembly as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Chapter 23-17 of the General Laws entitled "Licensing of Healthcare
2 Facilities" is hereby amended by adding thereto the following section:
3 23-17-9.1. Mandatory conversion to renewable energy.
4 (a) All healthcare facilities, as defined in ยง 23-17-2, shall, not later than January 1, 2026,
5 as a condition of maintaining their license issued pursuant to chapter 17 of title 23, begin to convert
6 from a reliance on fossil fuels for energy, to renewable fuels, energy sources and so called "green"
7 sources of energy that result in a reduction in energy consumption and cost.
8 (b) The department of business regulation, in consultation with the office of energy
9 resources and the department of health, shall promulgate rules and regulations to implement
10 subsection (a) of this section.
11 SECTION 2. This act shall take effect upon passage.
